The paper discusses the performance of the BERT language model in answering cloze-style questions, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR), hence cs.CL and cs.IR are likely categories. The paper also proposes an extension of BERT, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.AI and cs.LG are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of different models in unsupervised question answering, which falls under the category of neural networks and deep learning, hence cs.NE is also a likely category.
